Boil a large #pot of water for the udon noodles. Add the @Udon Noodles{300%grams} then
lower heat to medium-high and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%mins}. Once cooked,
drain in a #colander and pop back in the pot. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir
through to stop them sticking together. Keep covered.

Meanwhile, boil a medium #pot of water for the broccoli. Cut the @Broccoli{1} into
florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Halve, peel and thinly slice @Onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced) (double for
4p).

Peel and grate the @Garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the
@Ginger{1}.

Halve the @Lime{1}, squeeze the juice and set aside. Roughly chop the @Peanuts{40%grams}.

Cook the broccoli in the boiling water for ~{3%mins}. Drain and rinse under cold
water.

Meanwhile, add half the grated ginger to a #bowl for the dressing. Mix in
@oil{1%tbsp}(drizzle, double for 4p), @Soy Sauce{1%sachet}, @Balsamic Vinegar{1%sachet},
@Honey{1%sachet}, and lime juice. Add the chopped peanuts.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan on high heat. Fry the sliced onion and broccoli
for ~{6-8%mins}.

Add the garlic and the remaining ginger at the last minute.

Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}. Remove from the pan and set aside
covered.

Season the @Irish Beef Rump{250%grams} steaks with salt and pepper. Once the oil is
hot, lay them into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%min} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Lower the heat and cook for another ~{1-2%mins} each side if you want them
medium-rare. When done, transfer to a #board and allow to rest for a few mins. Steak
is safe to eat when outside is browned.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

Slice the beef into thin strips.

Divide the noodles between plates. Place the broccoli onion mix on top.

Top with the beef strips and drizzle over the ginger lime dressing.